theorem Topology.interior_compl_eq_compl_closure {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X} :
    interior (Aᶜ) = (closure A)ᶜ := by
  ext x
  constructor
  · intro hx
    -- We prove `x ∉ closure A` by contradiction.
    by_contra hMem
    -- Any open neighbourhood of `x` meets `A`; in particular `interior (Aᶜ)`.
    have hNon :
        ((interior (Aᶜ) : Set X) ∩ A).Nonempty :=
      (mem_closure_iff).1 hMem _ isOpen_interior hx
    rcases hNon with ⟨y, ⟨hyInt, hyA⟩⟩
    -- But `y ∈ interior (Aᶜ)` implies `y ∉ A`, contradiction.
    have : (y : X) ∈ Aᶜ :=
      (interior_subset : interior (Aᶜ) ⊆ Aᶜ) hyInt
    exact this hyA
  · intro hx
    -- Use the open set `(closure A)ᶜ` containing `x` and contained in `Aᶜ`.
    have hOpen : IsOpen ((closure A)ᶜ) :=
      (isClosed_closure (s := A)).isOpen_compl
    have hSub : ((closure A)ᶜ : Set X) ⊆ Aᶜ := by
      intro y hy
      by_contra hAy
      exact hy (subset_closure hAy)
    have hInt : ((closure A)ᶜ : Set X) ⊆ interior (Aᶜ) :=
      interior_maximal hSub hOpen
    exact hInt hx
